race.comment: ENZONI (6) went forward last start over 1370m at Bowraville and held on well for second, beaten half a length. Ticking along nicely now and doesn't have to improve much to go one better. AMALFI AMORE (4) has three placings from five runs this prep and last start finished 1.3 lengths from the winner in second over 1512m at Port Macquarie. Ready to find winning form. ASTROGAZER (1) went forward and gave a great sight before finishing third when resuming last time out over 1400m at Orange. Faces an easier assignment so he is all set to build on that latest effort. WARRANT (3) improved last start but found a couple better over 1512m at Port Macquarie, beaten just 1.75 lengths. Likely to hold the form and is a strong top-three prospect. NOT MY PROBLEM (8) was well below her best last time but her prior form measures right up. Don't underestimate.
